&lt;p&gt;Could this be related to Lu-4249. They are both the same filesystem&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think so, this is a client bug, whereas &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4249&quot; title=&quot;exception RIP: lqe64_hash_keycmp+12&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4249&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4249&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a server side problem, and not like the oqi hash on client, the server side lqe hash has reference count for each lqe, so it has no such race in theory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72679" author="mhanafi" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 06:02:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could this be related to Lu-4249. They are both the same filesystem&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72670" author="niu" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 02:00:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/8460&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/8460&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72668" author="niu" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 01:39:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1515870810 is 0x5a5a5a5a, which means the oqi in hash has been freed at this moment, looks there is an obvious race between osc_quota_setdq() and osc_quota_chkdq(). I&apos;ll cooke a patch to fix it soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
